  "prompt": "Which sect of Jews lived in Macca and Madinah during the time of Prophet Muhammad?",
  "response": "During the time of Prophet Muhammad, the Jewish community in the Arabian Peninsula included several sects, but in the cities of Makkah (Mecca) and Madinah (Medina), the Jews were primarily associated with a few specific tribes. In Medina, notable Jewish tribes included the Banu Qaynuqa, Banu Nadir, and Banu Qurayza. These tribes were involved in trade and had an established presence in the region. \n\nIn Makkah, there was a smaller Jewish community, and they were mainly traders. The overall Jewish presence in the region was more significant in Medina, where they had alliances and tensions with the Muslim community during Muhammad's time. \n\nThese Jewish tribes interacted with Muhammad and the early Muslim community, which involved periods of both alliance and conflict as the socio-political landscape evolved in the region.",
